DUBAI: Princess ‘Azemah Ni’matul Bolkiah — the daughter of one of the richest men in the world, the Sultan of Brunei — tied the knot this month in an extravagant traditional wedding. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle The 38-year-old princess, who is the eighth child of her billionaire father, got married to her first cousin, Prince Bahar ibni Jefri Bolkiah.  A post shared by Mateen (@tmski)  The week-long ceremony took place at the sultan’s opulent official residence, Istana Nurul Iman, which is located outside the capital city of Bandar Seri Bega. The celebrations featured a royal “powdering” ceremony, an Islamic signing ceremony and a glittering reception. The Islamic ceremony took place at the Omar ‘Ali Saifuddien Mosque, which is one of Brunei's national landmarks.  A post shared by Mateen (@tmski)  For the “powdering” ceremony, during which the couple’s family bless them with colored rice powder and scented oils, the bride dazzled in a pink full-length dress and gold jewelry. Meanwhile, for the reception, she wore a white, heavily embellished long-sleeved gown with a mermaid skirt. Her husband wore a white military uniform.